    <h1 class="text-center" style="margin-top: 10rem;">Netqube Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> 22/04/2025</p>
    <br><br>
    <p>This Privacy Policy describes how <strong>Netqube</strong> ("we", "our", or "us") collects, uses, and protects your personal information when you use our services, including our website and platform (collectively, the “Services”).</p>
    <br><br>
    <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>We may collect the following types of information:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> Name, email address, password, and any information you provide during signup.</li>
        <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> IP address, device type, browser, operating system, pages visited, and interactions with the Services.</li>
        <li><strong>Payment Information:</strong> Processed securely via third-party services (e.g., Stripe); we do not store card details.</li>
        <li><strong>Content You Provide:</strong> Files, text, or other materials uploaded to or processed by our platform.</li>
    </ul>
    <br><br>
    <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <p>We use your information to:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Provide and maintain our Services</li>
        <li>Authenticate and manage your account</li>
        <li>Respond to inquiries and provide support</li>
        <li>Improve, monitor, and personalize the Services</li>
        <li>Communicate updates, security alerts, and important notices</li>
        <li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
    </ul>
    <br><br>
    <h2>3. Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
    <p>We do not sell your personal data. We may share your information with trusted third parties in the following cases:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Service Providers:</strong> Companies that help us operate the platform (e.g., cloud storage, payment processing).</li>
        <li><strong>Legal Compliance:</strong> If required by law or to protect our legal rights or the safety of users.</li>
    </ul>
    <br><br>
    <h2>4. Cookies and Tracking</h2>
    <p>We use cookies and similar technologies to enhance your experience, analyze usage, and remember your preferences. You can manage your cookie preferences through your browser settings.</p>
    <br><br>
    <h2>5. Data Security</h2>
    <p>We take reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect your data. However, no method of transmission over the internet is 100% secure, so we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>
    <br><br>
    <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
    <p>We retain your personal information only as long as necessary to provide the Services and fulfill legal obligations. You may request deletion of your data at any time.</p>
    <br><br>
    <h2>7. Your Rights</h2>
    <p>You have the right to access, update, or delete your personal data. You may also object to certain processing activities or request data portability. To make a request, contact us at the email below.</p>
    <br><br>
    <h2>8. Children’s Privacy</h2>
    <p>Netqube is not intended for use by children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe a child has provided us data, please contact us for deletion.</p>
    <br><br>
    <h2>9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. We will notify you of material changes by posting an update on our website or through your account. Continued use of the Services constitutes acceptance.</p>
